>My reading of the English language seems to be somewhat different
>from Ed Hamrick's. His quoted material is shot through with what he
>calls "weasel words" and restrictions of all sorts, and is not as
>open and shut as he would like to make it seem. Apologies for not
>editing more than I've done--I'm only trying to show various
>kinds of restrictions in the language. Not all apply to the current
